#' CSEM: A Package for Computing Conditional Standard Errors of Measurement
#'
#' @description
#' The `CSEM` package provides functions for computing various methods of Conditional
#' Standard Error of Measurement (CSEM), including:
#'
#' - **MF-CSEM**: Mollenkopf-Feldt method
#' - **Thorndike-CSEM**: Based on half-test differences
#' - **Binomial-CSEM**: Based on the binomial model
#' - **Other Reliability-Based Methods**
#'
#' Additionally, the package includes tools for:
#' - Splitting test items into halves (`check.split`)
#' - Computing reliability estimates (`check.alpha`, `check.angoff`, `check.omega`,
#' `check.spearmanbrown`)
#' - Testing the distribution of split scores (`check.distribution`, `calculate.OVI`)
#' - Visualizing results (`check.plot`)
#' - Testing differences between location parameter of halves (`check.location`)
#' - Testing differences between scale parameter of halves (`check.scale`)
#' - Computing standardized CSEM (`std.CSEM`)
#'
#' @section Getting Started:
#' To install and load the package, run:
#'
#' ```r
#' install.packages("CSEM")
#' library(CSEM)
#' ```
#'
#' @section Example Usage:
#' ```r
#' # Compute MF-CSEM
#' MF.CSEM(half1 = dhalf1, half2 = dhalf2, data = dataset, reliability.coef = 0.9,
#'         n.items = 6, min.score.item = 0, max.score.item = 4, conf.level = .95)
#' ```
#'
#' @docType package
#' @name CSEM
NULL
